The paper discusses the development of a mobile 3D printing system that requires solving motion planning, localization, and motion control problems specific to robotics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of computer vision (cs.CV) for localization and motion planning, as well as graphics (cs.GR) for visualization of the printed structure. The paper also involves the use of multimedia (cs.MM) for demonstrating the printing-while-moving experiment. Finally, the paper involves the use of control systems (cs.SY) for motion control of the robot arm.
